[2] Nigeria - suspected cases and WHO DG statement
Date: Sun 12 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Agence France Presse (AFP), Sun 12 Feb 2006 [edited]
<http://www.africasia.com/services/news/newsitem.php?area=africa&item=060212095315.763dus8n.php>

Nigeria: 2 Children Are Suspected Avian Influenza Cases
-----------------------------------------------
Nigerian doctors are testing blood samples from 2 children they
suspect may have been infected with the deadly H5N1 strain of bird
flu, a senior health ministry official said on Sunday [12 Feb 2006].
"We've taken their samples, which are now undergoing some laboratory
tests," said Nasidi Yakubu, a director from the Federal Health
Ministry deployed to northern Nigeria to monitor Africa's 1st
outbreak of the disease.
--
